<br>
Originally, I was glad to see the MB re-tune, happy for my mage friends (and sad as a raider), and pissed for my monk twink.....<br>
<br>
Then I thought about it....<br>
My monkey is my first twink, and at level 21, he's really not that far behind my 46 warrior.  So, a little nerfage ain't too bad.  I see folks re-learnin' the fine art of the pull, perhaps an extra monk or two to &quot;tag&quot; things off, bards/rangers/druids in outdoor zones, and heck, one of the best pullers I've ever seen was my friend Aanthan, pullin' juggs in Sebilis.... and he's a 'Chanter!!!<br>
<br>
All-in-all, will make things a bit tough 'til the finish the &quot;re-tunes&quot;, and patch about 10 times to get it all right, and release PoP right in the middle.  <br>
<br>
Moro, if yer really gonna quit, think about one thing... in about 1-2 weeks of play time with that char, you could FD PL any class you wanted to at least 50, dependin' on how much time you have.  I don't know you that well, but best of luck to ya if you do leave.  /salute<br>
<br>
('twould be interestin' if all the monkey's just started a new char.  /shrug)<br>
