<br>
As I only have a YOUNG wizard I cannot comment n the whole MB thing. However, many a thread have been started because a few &quot;yahoo's&quot; MB'd a dragon as another raid was getting ready to engage. In lieu of this, I welcome the change.<br>
<br>
Also, VI stated that they are NOT getting rid of the skill, they are only making the burnable mobs gain a &quot;latent&quot; effect from being burned, so they can't be burned again within a certain amount of time (1 minute was used as an example).<br>
<br>
As a cleric, I have never understood why a complete heal would heal for 10,200 hp's, when NO ONE (pc) in the game had that many hp's (most i've seen is like 6,500 buffed). I welcome this change as it allows VI to introduce and tinker with newer more aggresive heals.<br>
<br>
Personally, as a Cleric, I usually have issues with monks. for some reason they think they can &quot;take a lickin and keep on tickin&quot; better than warriors. IE.. They gain agro in a fight AND KEEP IT!! They refuse to FD, until JUST after I healed them (go figure), and even then they would complain. Some monks can take 4 maybe 5 hits before I need to heal them, thus wasting my mana if I need to heal them every 5 hits. For god's sake.. learn to FD.. tanks are TANKS for a reason!!<br>
<br>
I see many monks switching classes.<br>
<br>
I also have a YOUNG mage, not yet able to conjure mod rods. However, being on many raids, I see this as a double edged sword. Many a Magi complained that they were tired of having to mod rod through an entire battle (in reality it was usually prior to battle, they just had no mana during battle). Well, THOSE Magi's got their wish. No longer will they be forced to Mod Rod for the entire raid prior to battle. NOW.. they will do it DURING the actual fight. (see the double edge?)<br>
<br>
I do feel for the Magi's, as having played a younger level, I see great potential in them. But CoTH and mod rods do not do them justice.<br>
